(ii) Starting Wireshark
Answer:

To start Wireshark, follow these steps:

Click Start → Search → Wireshark, then open it.

The main window shows a list of available network interfaces.

Choose the active interface (e.g., Wi-Fi, Ethernet).

Click on the Start Capture (blue shark fin) icon to begin capturing packets.

The packets will start appearing in the Packet List Pane.

To stop, click on the Stop button (red square).

Note:
Wireshark can capture live packets only if you have proper permissions (administrator/root access).

Output:
Captured packets appear in real time with their source, destination, protocol, and info fields.
